{"key":"processedPost-17093158","value":{"id":17093158,"first":17093081,"last":17093278,"when":1351116114,"utime":"10/25/12 01:01 AM","content":"The 6\" depth ones are generally superior to clean room filters, which are often 12\" thick, but have a lower resistance.&nbsp; You want the higher resistance because it helps create laminar flow.&nbsp; 99.97% @ .3 microns is the flowhood hepa standard.<br /><br />You study the chart that comes with the filter to determine the right sized blower.&nbsp; Don't try to do it in the opposite direction.&nbsp; Shoot for an airspeed of roughly 100 to 125 linear feet per minute leaving the hood.<br /><br />You can just cover the face with cardboard when moving it or for storage.<br />RR","title":"Re: Building a flowhood. HEPA Q","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}